        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_0</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>**What we're doing with Drop That Beat Like an Ugly Baby** (*Because it's a game people are pissed off at us about for taking so long, but we will get the goddamned thing finished if I have to program the rest of it with my teeth.*)</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_1</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>If you're unfamiliar with the game, it lives here: http://www.subject2236.com/kickit If you're familiar with the game, you know that we've taken about a year longer to get to the point we're now at than we expected.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_2</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>I'll repeat what I've said before: this is my fault. **</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_3</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>I fucked up.**</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_4</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Here's what we're doing to do next: **1.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_5</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>We're going to finish the damned game.**</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_6</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>By way of substantiation, here's how we've been updating it in the past few months: ============================================================= **March 20th, 2013** Update Name: OhNoILostMySpacebarAgain Weve been continuing to integrate your feedback into the game.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_7</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Here's the latest: GAMEPLAY: Weve taken two of our levels, and put you in control via the Genetics Lab.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_8</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>When you unlock cities Five and Six, youre able to control the level's DNA via three variables: FATNESS, SPREAD and SALT.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_9</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Take some screenshots or videos of what your levels look like; were looking forward to what you guys come up with.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_10</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>FEEDBACK: Weve temporarily replaced the proximity sensor (the big circle on the screen) with some pretty awesome particle effects that show up when you get close to stuff.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_11</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>We also added some popups to show you when and where youve done some stunts.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_12</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>How does it look?</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_13</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>VISUALS: Michael just finished laying the groundwork for a new background visualizer.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_14</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>At its very basic level, it allows us to easily animate the background color of the world as youre flying through it.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_15</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>It also will let us create some animated and awesome background imagery to further enhance your experience.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_16</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>If you have any ideas for visualizers, please feel free to share them.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_17</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>ANALYSIS: There was a last minute improvement to BeatBox, our song analysis tech.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_18</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>This update helps us *much* more accurately detect beats for EDM and bass-heavy songs.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_19</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>One last thing: were playing with the idea of letting you rotate yourself within the world.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_20</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Press the mouse buttons to rotate left or right.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_21</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>How does it feel?</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_22</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Do you think thatd be a fun addition for gameplay?</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_23</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Weve got a few ideas were going to keep under our collective hats right now.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_24</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Did you notice that Dave was wearing a hat in our video?</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_25</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>He always does that.. whats he hiding under there?</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_26</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>As always, tell us what you love, what you hate, and what youre doing this weekend. (</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_27</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Well be at PAX East!)</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_28</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>============================================================= **March 1st, 2013** Update Name: The Fattest Baby is the Cutest Hey everyone!</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_29</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Some gritty details of our work: - Stunts!</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_30</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Nine of them!</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_31</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Build up a huge combo, but be careful to not risk it all! -</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_32</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>A level select, and three different levels for you to play in.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_33</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Tell us what you like about each of them, and which ones you like most. -</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_34</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Performance improvements to balance out the crazy colors that we've been throwing into the game. -</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_35</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>You can take screenshots now, just hit F12 at any time.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_36</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>They'll be in the "Screenshots" folder in the game directory. -</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_37</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>A proximity sensor.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_38</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>A segmented circle shows up where nearby things are to you, and how close you're getting to them. -</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_39</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Caching for some of our level loading stuff, so you should be seeing faster load times. -</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_40</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Three new songs! (</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_41</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Two from Morgan Packard, and another one from Hybrid Mind Studios) The feedback from you guys has been absolutely awesome so far, development continues to move along.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_42</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>We decided to take a chunk of time and dedicate February to really refining where we want the gameplay to go.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_43</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>This build should show a great base for where we're going.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_44</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Previously we had you collect two different types of pickups.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_45</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>One for Signal, which increases your multiplier and beautifies the level, and another simply for points.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_46</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Some of you mentioned wanting to do more than that, so we took that feedback and folded it into a brand-new stunt system!</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_47</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>It builds off of some gameplay reminiscient to Aaaaa!</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_48</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>If you pass by an object quickly, you get a buzz.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_49</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>If you pass alongside an object for an extended amount of time, you get a groove.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_50</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>As you build combinations and perturbations of these movements, you'll be able to discover up to eight different stunts we've thrown in, AS A START.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_51</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>We're pretty excited about this whole thing, we think it's going to open up a whole new way for you to re-experience and explore your music.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_52</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Tell us what you think.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_53</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Known things: - Unicode song names still doesn't work.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_54</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>============================================================= **February 1st, 2013** Update Name: Task Master Changes Ichiro says: Our goal was to bump the fun up one notch and get the music-to-level connection up one notch. (</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_55</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>We ain't there yet, but we're closer!)</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_56</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>We've started looking at individual songs and considering how they should look in the game.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_57</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>For example, we wanted Enya's A Day Without Rain to feel open and free, like a toddler who's simultaneously discovered the twin concepts of nudity and running down the street.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_58</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>So, when the game hears a song that's low-energy, the playing field opens up all big-like, and the obstacles leave.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_59</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>We're also just now starting to make different songs feel different in other ways.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_60</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>We run what we call a mutator over a level on certain tracks, so if you try a handful of different ones, you should see some variation between them.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_61</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Known Issues: - The game still chokes on files with unicode characters.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_62</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Youll have to rename it in order to play it for now, sorry. -</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_63</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>More excuses incoming!</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_64</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>============================================================= **January 25th, 2013** Update Name: Nasty Butler We hope you guys had a great new year.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_65</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>We spent some time chewing on your feedback, drinking far too much eggnog, and stretching our legs with the tools that weve built so far.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_66</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>This update continues to focus on making gameplay more fun, and making visuals feel even more visceral.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_67</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Changelog: - New Mechanics!</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_68</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Collecting signal truly plays into the visual feel of the game now, and affects the multiplier of our brand-spanking-new secondary point pickup.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_69</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Max out your signal and grab as many points as you can.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_70</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Point multiplier from 1x to 3x depending on your signal %. (</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_71</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Twist: Signal drains slowly during normal gameplay.) -</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_72</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>The level constricts and expands depending on the feel of the song you're listening to. -</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_73</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Added mousewheel scrolling to the filebrowser - No less than 537 optimizations.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_74</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>The game should run beautifully and smoothly on your toaster. -</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_75</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Added a crosshair, and tweaked the movement and camera angle a good bit. (</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_76</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Protip: Weve added three different crosshairs.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_77</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Press F1 to toggle between all of them.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_78</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Tell us which one is your favorite.)</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_79</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Known Issues: - The game still chokes on files with unicode characters.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_80</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Youll have to rename it in order to play it for now, sorry. -</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_81</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>E-mail rshenoy@subject2236.com with a convincing complaint about all the Reddit spam he's been putting out.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_82</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>The most convincing person will get an alpha key to Drunken Robot Pornography, because why not. -</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_83</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Thats it, were only allowed to have one bug in the game.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_84</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>============================================================= **December 21st, 2012** Update Name: Rabid Wumpus That's two updates in one month.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_85</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>We are not kidding around here.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_86</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Our focus at the moment is SPEED.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_87</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Does the game feel like it's more fun than the first build for its fastness?</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_88</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>We'll make it more fun in other ways as well -- more mechanics, better controls.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_89</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Maybe WASD or gamepad, as Wuggly says.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_90</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>But right now, think "speed."</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_723_116_91</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Thanks for reading.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
